      • prepare

        public void prepare()
        Description copied from interface: Locks.Client
        Start preparing this transaction for committing. In two-phase locking palace, we will in principle no longer be acquiring any new locks - though we still allow it because it is useful in certain technical situations - but when we are ready, we will start releasing them. This also means that we will no longer accept being asynchronously stopped. From this point on, only the commit process can decide if the transaction lives or dies, and in either case, the lock client will end up releasing all locks via the Locks.Client.close() method.
        Specified by:
        prepare in interface Locks.Client

      • stop

        public void stop()
        Description copied from interface: Locks.Client
        Stop all active lock waiters and release them. All new attempts to acquire any locks will cause exceptions. This client can and should only be closed afterwards. If this client has been prepared, then all currently acquired locks will remain held, otherwise they will be released immediately.
        Specified by:
        stop in interface Locks.Client
